  <datafield tag="500" ind1=" " ind2=" ">
    <subfield code="a">Esther Sturge was prevented from writing because of illness in the family. The &quot;serious indisposition&quot; of Esther Sturge&apos;s brother was for some weeks very alarming. Esther Sturge finds the progress of anti-slavery principles in America delightful. She asks how it is that funds are so low in Boston just now.</subfield>
  </datafield>
  <datafield tag="500" ind1=" " ind2=" ">
    <subfield code="a">In the postscript, Esther Sturge explains that her brevity is the result of gout, which has made her &quot;hand almost useless.&quot; She mentions also that they still hope to have a Peace Convention in August in Paris. She believes that Frederick Douglass is now in London.</subfield>
